This paper is about using tensor networks for image classification, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper is primarily focused on applying a machine learning technique (tensor networks) to image classification. The second most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as image classification is a core problem in computer vision. The third most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as machine learning is a subfield of AI. The fourth most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper discusses the use of automatic gradients for optimization, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks. The fifth most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as tensor networks are a type of data structure used in this paper.
